I thought this would spark some good ideas, some interesting conversation, and some positive comments.  Apparently not. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub59.ezboard.com/ujaraxalle.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jaraxalle</A> at: 10/10/02 2:56:04 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub59.ezboard.com/umigatolsmashmouth.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Migatol Smashmouth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Scowls at you rdy to attack!</span><br>  Posts: 13<br> <font color=#333333>(10/10/02 4:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub59.ezboard.com/fguild75784frm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11.topic&index=44>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Epic Upgrad</span><hr size=1> The value of the warrior epic is not in it's damage delay, it's all in the stats and the proc.<br>
<br>
First off the warrior epics provide +15 STA and +100 HPs, that's roughly +190 HPs overall, which is very nice. Next they give +10 to all resists, also a very nice bonus especially since the resist revamp.<br>
<br>
But the most valuable part of the epics is the Rage of Vallon proc. That gives you 500 points of agro, and does a 100 point DD. It procs a lot, I usually get at least 5+ procs per fight, that amounts to about 2500 points of agro and 500 points of damage per fight while grinding and far more on big mobs like dragons.<br>
<br>
There's only one other 1-hand slash in game that delivers direct increase of agro similar to the Rage Vallon in the game, that would be Bloodfrenzy which is off Vyzh`dra the Cursed in Ssraeahza Temple.<br>
<br>
So to tell you the truth, yes the warrior epic doesn't have a superior damage/delay, but it is a very good set of warrior swords as the 1hs versions. Considering the difficulty of acquiring the warrior epic, it's a nice reward in my opinion, because we get exactly what we want and need, the ability to get more agro. Beyond level 55, it means so much to keep agro.<br>
<br>
Our job as warriors are to be the &quot;Main Tanks&quot; we take damage, we are the big guys. How many times have you been in Plane of Hate and a Spite Golem is beating the crap out of a Ranger, while you are pounding on the Taunt key trying to peel it off of him? When the warriors can get and keep agro, everyone else can spend their time beating up the mob that is being fought. A dead grind group or raid party is no fun when you are the last one standing because you have the most HPs. LOL, believe me, I know it well, I've been there 100 times.<br>
<br>
Since I have a set of warrior epics, I can tell you they are excellent weapons, and if they were to upgrade them, I wouldn't complain. But as is, I am happy.<br>
